\chapter{Tolima}  

This is a survey of the postage stamps and postal history of Tolima.
Tolima is one of the 32 departments of [Colombia](../colombia/introduction), located in the Andean region, in the center-west of the country. The department of Tolima was created in 1861 from a part of what was previously Cundinamarca.

First stamps

The first stamps of Tolima were issued in 1870.[1]

